1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - This paper analyzes the temporal evolution of digital communication activity related to the Occupy Wall Street movement on Twitter. 2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper may also fall under this category as it involves the analysis of a large volume of data from Twitter using various software tools and techniques. 

3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The Occupy Wall Street movement is a social movement, and this paper examines its digital evolution. It may be relevant to the study of the impact of technology on society, which falls under this category. 

4. cs.CS (Computer Science) - The paper involves the analysis of data using computational techniques, which is a core aspect of computer science. 

5. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper examines the behavior of users on Twitter in relation to the Occupy Wall Street movement, which is related to social and behavioral sciences.
